PART 2Ô∏è‚É£ ‚Äî UNDERSTANDING DEFAULT LOGIN LOGIC

app/Http/Controllers/Auth/AuthenticatedSessionController.php

public function store(LoginRequest $request)
{
    $request->authenticate();
    $request->session()->regenerate();

    return redirect()->intended(RouteServiceProvider::HOME);
}

app/Http/Requests/Auth/LoginRequest.php

public function rules()
{
    return [
        'email' => ['required', 'email'],
        'password' => ['required'],
    ];
}

PART 3Ô∏è‚É£ ‚Äî CUSTOM LOGIN LOGIC (IMPORTANT üî•)

 Login Only Active Users
app/Http/Requests/Auth/LoginRequest.php

public function authenticate()
{
    if (! Auth::attempt([
        'email' => $this->email,
        'password' => $this->password,
        'status' => 1
    ])) {
        throw ValidationException::withMessages([
            'email' => 'Invalid credentials or inactive account.',
        ]);
    }
}

 Custom Username Login (Instead of Email)

public function rules()
{
    return [
        'username' => ['required'],
        'password' => ['required'],
    ];
}

 Authenticate Logic
Auth::attempt([
    'username' => $this->username,
    'password' => $this->password,
]);

 Role-Based Login Redirect

app/Http/Controllers/Auth/AuthenticatedSessionController.php

if (auth()->user()->role === 'admin') {
    return redirect('/admin/dashboard');
}

return redirect('/dashboard');

PART 4Ô∏è‚É£ ‚Äî PROTECT ROUTES USING AUTH

routes/web.php

Route::middleware('auth')->group(function () {
    Route::get('/dashboard', function () {
        return view('dashboard');
    });
});

PART 5Ô∏è‚É£ ‚Äî CUSTOM LOGIN (WITHOUT BREEZE) üî•

If interviewer asks manual auth logic üëá

1Ô∏è‚É£ Create Controller
php artisan make:controller AuthController

app/Http/Controllers/AuthController.php

use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Auth;
use Illuminate\Http\Request;

class AuthController extends Controller
{
    public function login(Request $request)
    {
        $credentials = $request->only('email', 'password');

        if (Auth::attempt($credentials)) {
            return redirect('/dashboard');

}

        return back()->withErrors(['email' => 'Invalid login']);
    }

    public function logout()
    {
        Auth::logout();
        return redirect('/login');
    }
}

2Ô∏è‚É£ Routes

 routes/web.php

Route::post('/login', [AuthController::class, 'login']);
Route::post('/logout', [AuthController::class, 'logout']);
